title: Don't Handle Some Exceptions
message:
Don't Handle Some Exceptions

In Kotlin, exceptions don't have to be checked. In most scenarios in
our code, the exceptions are just logged, which isn't very useful, and
the same generic code was used almost everywhere.

Since there is no requirement to check exceptions, and since we weren't
doing much with our checking, we may as well remove these sections of
our code.

than relying upon activities. Due to this change, increase the version

This is almost a complete redo of a lot of the stuff, with the

checks to prevent some potential bugs. Up and back navigation have
been implemented properly as well.
